<docs>
   <doc for="ListViewDesigner">
 <summary>
 <para>Provides design-time functionality for the <see cref='System.Windows.Forms.ListView'/> 
 control.</para>
 </summary>
 <remarks>
    <para>This designer implements hit testing for the items in 
       the list view control.</para>
 </remarks>
 <seealso cref='System.Windows.Forms.ListView'/>
   </doc>
   <doc for="ListViewDesigner.GetHitTest">
 <summary>
    <para>Indicates whether the specified point was within the bounds of the component.</para>
 </summary>
 <returns>
 <para><see langword='true'/> if the specified point should be considered
    "active"; <see langword='false'/> if it is not something the user can
    interact with.</para>
 </returns>
 <remarks>
 <para><see cref='System.Windows.Forms.Design.ListViewDesigner.GetHitTest'/> 
 provides a way to allow your tree view component to support a design-time user
 interface by indicating when the tree view design-time functionality must be
 used.</para>
 </remarks>
   </doc>
   <doc for="ListViewDesigner.WndProc">
 <summary>
    <para>Provides support for Windows message processing.</para>
 </summary>
   </doc>
</docs>

